[[Image:lucas bolsius.jpg|right|250px|Bolsius at work, 2007]]
'''Lucas Bolsius''' (born 16 December 1958 in [[The Hague]], [[South Holland]]) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[historian]] and politician of the [[Christian Democratic Appeal]] and since 31 August 2010 mayor of the city of [[Amersfoort]].
Bolsius studied [[social history]] at [[Erasmus University Rotterdam]]. He was a member of the [[States of South Holland]] for the [[Christian Democratic Appeal]] between 1995 and 1998. In 1998 he became member of the municipal council of [[Rotterdam]] for the same party.<ref name=amersfoort>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.amersfoort.nl/4/Burgemeester/Curriculum-Vitae.html|title=Curriculum Vitae burgemeester|publisher=Municipality of Amersfoort|date=|accessdate=8 March 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402101451/http://www.amersfoort.nl/4/Burgemeester/Curriculum-Vitae.html|archivedate=2 April 2015|df=}}</ref> He performed several jobs before becoming a full-time politician in 2002 when he became an alderman of the [[municipality]] of [[Rotterdam]]. His responsibilities included social affairs, [[quarter (country subdivision)|quarters]] and [[public space]]. After the 2006 elections he continued as alderman. This time his responsibilities include financial affairs, sports and public space.<ref name=amersfoort/>
